com.gemstone.gemfire.cache.hdfs

Interface HDFSStoreFactory


  • public interface HDFSStoreFactory
    Factory for creating instances of HDFSStore. To get an instance of this factory call Cache#createHDFSStoreFactory.

    Usage

    1. configure factory using set methods
    2. call create(java.lang.String) to produce a HDFSStore instance.

      • create

        HDFSStore create(java.lang.String name)
          throws GemFireConfigException,
                 StoreExistsException
        Validates all attribute values and assigns defaults where applicable. Creates a new instance of HDFSStore based on the current attribute values configured in this factory.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the HDFSStore
        Returns:
        the newly created HDFSStore.
        Throws:
        GemFireConfigException - if the configuration is invalid
        StoreExistsException - if a HDFSStore with the same name exists
